cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL 

The paper focuses on using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for visual sentiment prediction, which is a task related to computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the analysis of the network's architecture, which could be related to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
